<p>PTSD is a disorder that can affect a person if they have experienced or witnessed a traumatic event. Sleep issues can be some of the most challenging aspects of having PTSD. Common sleep difficulties include insomnia and nightmares. People with PTSD may have intense nightmares that occur regularly. These nightmares may include replays of the traumatic event or events that caused the person to develop PTSD. One brand name for the drug is Minipress.</p>
<p>Doctors usually prescribe prazosin to treat high blood pressure as it widens the blood vessels, allowing the blood to flow more easily. However, doctors also prescribe prazosin off-label to treat PTSD-associated nightmares. Prazosin has an affect on alpha-1 receptors that are present on smooth muscle tissue, including the blood vessel walls and the brain. This results in the relaxation of these smooth muscles, leading to a decrease in blood pressure. It is also able to cross the blood-brain barrier, which may help treat PTSD-associated nightmares.</p>
<p>However, the evidence is mixed. One clinical trial included a number of military veterans with PTSD. The trial concluded that prazosin did not alleviate distressing dreams or improve sleep quality. More research is needed to determine whether prazosin is an effective treatment for PTSD nightmares. More serious but less common side effects include hypotension, or low blood pressure. First-dose hypotension can be serious, so doctors recommend that a person takes their initial dose at night.</p>
<p>A person taking prazosin may also develop syncope, which is another name for fainting. There are also some very rare side effects. If a person takes prazosin and experiences any severe side effects, including fainting, weakness, tachycardia, impotence, or orthostatic hypotension, they should consider alternative treatments. If a person is taking other medications, they should always check with a doctor before taking prazosin. This is because it may interact with other medications. One of the possible side effects of prazosin is low blood pressure.</p>

